---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Projects" description="Case studies for SuperFIB and Stokvel Society.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container page-hero-layout">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="page-intro">Case studies</div>
        <h1 class="page-title">Projects that prove how I engineer.</h1>
        <p class="page-copy">
          These are not gallery pieces. They are systems where architecture, data flow, and trust matter more than cosmetic novelty.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="manifest">
        <div class="manifest-row">
          <strong>What I highlight</strong>
          <p>I focus on constraints, architecture decisions, and how the system behaves under pressure, not just the surface result.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="manifest-row">
          <strong>What I keep private</strong>
          <p>I show topology and engineering judgment without exposing formulas, thresholds, or sensitive business logic.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container project-list">
      <article class="project-entry">
        <div class="project-entry-header">
          <div class="stack-lg">
            <div class="eyeline">Trading infrastructure</div>
            <h2 class="project-name">SMC SuperFIB</h2>
            <p class="panel-copy">
              A cross-runtime execution and monitoring system that synchronises indicator logic, API state, trading clients, and dashboard visibility around one source of truth.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tag-row">
            <span class="tag">Pine Script</span>
            <span class="tag">MT5</span>
            <span class="tag">React</span>
            <span class="tag">WordPress API</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-layout">
          <div class="diagram-panel">
            <div class="diagram-frame">
              <img src="/images/diagram-system/superfib.svg" alt="SuperFIB system diagram showing the indicator, source-of-truth API, MT5 expert advisors, and dashboard." />
            </div>
            <p class="diagram-caption">The architecture keeps the API authoritative while the execution and dashboard layers stay readable for operators.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="info-stack">
            <div class="panel">
              <div class="panel-title">What made it hard</div>
              <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li>Parity across different runtimes and trading surfaces.</li>
                <li>State drift caused by timing differences and stale inputs.</li>
                <li>Operator trust when the UI and the execution layer disagree.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <a href="/projects/superfib" class="link-inline">Read the full SuperFIB case study</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="project-entry">
        <div class="project-entry-header">
          <div class="stack-lg">
            <div class="eyeline">Community finance</div>
            <h2 class="project-name">Stokvel Society</h2>
            <p class="panel-copy">
              A fintech platform for contribution tracking, trust-layer ledger handling, and payout visibility designed around clarity for members and administrators.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tag-row">
            <span class="tag">Astro</span>
            <span class="tag">Ledger logic</span>
            <span class="tag">Reporting</span>
            <span class="tag">Product UX</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-layout">
          <div class="diagram-panel">
            <div class="diagram-frame">
              <img src="/images/diagram-system/stokvel-society.svg" alt="Stokvel Society diagram showing contribution flow into a ledger and onward to payouts." />
            </div>
            <p class="diagram-caption">The product focuses on keeping money movement understandable, auditable, and easy to verify.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="info-stack">
            <div class="panel">
              <div class="panel-title">What made it hard</div>
              <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li>Translating trust-heavy community workflows into dependable software behavior.</li>
                <li>Keeping contribution and payout state readable for non-technical users.</li>
                <li>Balancing straightforward product language with serious financial responsibility.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <a href="/projects/stokvel" class="link-inline">Read the full Stokvel Society case study</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
